<p dir="auto">One of the things that has made pushing this to the kernel more difficult, however, is that for the GoXLR there are two parts to the initialisation. The first, as with the Blender is audio activation, which can be in the kernel, the second is the vendor specific configuration interface setup, which arguably shouldn't. While it's related to the device, it's strictly speaking not related to audio (it's also useless by itself without the utility). Even if the GoXLR audio setup was available in the kernel, most of the device would still be unusable without the util, which would have to continue doing the 'initialisation' phase, which is unfortunately where everything diverges slightly.</p>
<p dir="auto">With that being said, when I get home from vacation, I'll do some double checking on the initialiser, and review the pcap to see if I can get you something at least interim to get audio working nicely.</p>

